values:
wow i havent used this since october. holy smokes. 

i dont really have anything to say. my night sucked, football game with marching band and then argument with parents + grounded. i talked to claire on the phone for a little. that was definatly the highlight of my night. im going to bed now.

www.myspace.com/thedominotheory we have a new song.
i dont know what to write. they are both just too cool.

ok so im excited about this month of october. tdt and mundo rojo are doing a split and we're recording the weekend of the 22nd. we finally have another show lined up, october 30th at the ywca. and we have one november 5th at fennarios with out buds mundo rojo. practice yesterday, we wrote a new song, well started to at least, we actually started two and didnt like the first so went to subway and did the second later. we have a new pahardcore site and we have new buttons. we also have a new site, same address but the sites all different and new. www.tdthome.cjb.net

yesterday was my last day of band camp, i am glad. after it was over carolyn and i drove to grand slam were we met up with joe pat alyssa and emily, it was sort of fun. then alyssa and emily left and al and a different emily showed up. that was fun, and less awkward. pat and joe left shortly after that and i went to friendlys while carolyn al and emily went to dans. friendlys was boring until i saw ben and travis walking by.

ben travis and i went over to that temperary living/hotel place and looked inside peoples windows. it was fun. then i left and went home.

now im working on honors history work which totally sucks, i think im just going to not turn it in. i hope they dont test us on the book we were supposed to read. phoebes emailing me the idenifications because shes awesome and it didnt work when drew sent them. hopefully it works this time. i also hope that the journal entries/quotes arent worth alot of points because im not doing them.

tonights the show at the paul green school of rock, it should be alot of fun. im going. you should go too. the low budgets are playing and they rock. i love them.

emily and i just broke up.i dont really know her reason.she didnt really tell me.but for me.it wasnt going anywhere.it didnt seem that she really liked me the way i did.i dont know.i think it'll be good to move on. we dated for like 7 months.and sadly our relationship never really went anywhere.oh well.i guess thats what happens when you suck at life.yeah so i think what im trying to say is.yes.we did break up again.for a third time.for the third time.and the last time.this actually kind of sucks.

leftover fucking crack bitches!

band camp sucks! i hate it! it is sooo boring and mr. search is really annoying me. thank goodness i have vince or id probally go crazy. we hung out yesterday and had a blast, i got to play his bass...sooo nice, such a nice amp too. hes so fun. i love vince. emily comes home today, i think. i hope she calls me when she gets home because i want to tell her how cool i am. just kidding. tdt show tomorrow at the ywca, its going to be soo much fun, i havent played there in forever. i hope we dont mess up as much as we usually do, which is alot. we have two new songs for all of you, fasties. capitol risk has a new song everyone who cares, its on their purevolume site. i like it. their new singer is kind of not good though. ew fast food makes me sick. i always feel like shit after eating it. ok well im off to patricks, talk to you kids later.

my mother signed me up for golf camp at the upper main line ymca. it is one of the most boring things i have ever done. we putted for 2 hours today, then we chipped. if we hadnt played nine holes i think i would have walked home. its me and 3 little boys, a dorky one whos really funny to listen to, a gangster 10 year old who makes the most hilarious turtle faces, and a black kid who is extremly close minded. i hate summer reading, ive read 5 books this summer and only one has been for school, i still have to read two more and then do a journal on one of them for honors history. i hope i get to see emily before she leaves for the bahammas sunday. that'd be very nice. i hurt my finger and im tired because i only got 4 hours of sleep last night so im going to go. have fun boys and girls!
hey, theres a show on the 21st. go. its at the ywca. bye.

today was alright, i went to dereks with pat and pat. that was fun. now its raining and i cant do anything outside (skate). i have to go somewhere with my mom in a little bit, i dont really want to. i leave friday for new mexico, im going on a two week backpacking trip. hopefully i have a good time. it stinks because i won't be able to see Emily, let alone talk to her, the entire time. the day after i get home i have to go to boy scout camp, which totally sucks. im going to be soo tired and annoyed that week, i can see it. oh well, i'll live. i hope i get to see Emily when i get back, i hope shes home and not in bermuda or where ever she is going. that would stink. tdt's new cd is out so go buy it...actually we'll probaly end up giving it to you for free. bye bye.

wow i havent writen in this in a while! ok last night i went to a 4th of july party, and alyssa was there so we talked the whole time. it was alot of fun, i have never talked to her that much before. i skated with some boy for a little too, but that was before she got there. im thinking about becomming a vegetarian, but im not sure if i could do it. so right now im just eating all organic foods, which i have been doing for a while actually. bones brigade was absolutly fantastic on saturday. i love them. i saw emily too at that show which was really great. alright well i have to go. have a fun night.
<3 Andy Pants

tdt's new cd will be out within the next week. ken is supposed to drop it off sometime soon, and then we'll burn hundreds and put them in little cases for you kids. it'll be great. we havent thought up a price yet, probaly $2 or something like that, they wont be much dont worry. the cd's called "overdose" and it has 7 songs on it, i think, it might have 8. it includes our newest song "joe knows" and it rocks, you should all buy it once we have it. but enough with the greatness of tdt and on to next weekend...

Saturday, July 3rd - BONES BRIGADE, THE LOW BUDGETS, AND KNIFIGHT at the WAYNE TRAIN STATION CAFE, 6:30 to 10:30 - $6 

the domino theory may be playing also, more TBA.

contact: tdtcontact@hotmail.com

......today i got out of school at 9:30.tomorrow is the same.but tomorrow will be better.because i get to see emily.were going to the park.i miss her.i hope this thing works.....

show saturday at the wayne train station, odds against, the domino theory, kill you in the face, a sence of belonging, and etc, 6-11, $5. etc... is playing. everyone should come out, its the first wayne show in a while. katy wants me to go to fennarios with her, but no no no, its wayne for me, sorry katy. come to wayne hun, its going to rock.

emily asked me who i kissed at the end of the day today. i dont remember kissing anyone but travis, and she asked who the pretty girl, GIRL, was and travis is a guy, i think. maybe she thought i kissed jamals little sister zara, she walked me to my bus, well pats bus but still. i didnt kiss her though, we were just talking, shes really nice. emily said peter and dustin gave her $20 and said she could keep it if she found out who i kissed, but i never kissed anyone. weird. 

anyway, this week has been really crappy. emily and i broke up after 5 months. my longest relationship with a girl. she said she didnt want to go out over summer because we'd never see each other, she said something about not wanting to do something that might make me not like her too, it was really confusing and really, really unexpected. ive been pretty sad all week, like ill be happy and then something will remind me of her and ill get all depressed, and it sucks. she said shes going to come to my bands show saturday so we can hang out, but we have hardly talked at all since the breakup so i think its going to be awkward. oh well, at least ill get to see her. i really like her alot. everyones telling me to move on and i know thats probally what i should do, but i dont really want to, and im not doing a good job at it considering im planing on hanging out with her saturday night. i dont think i want to get over her, but maybe i should? argh this sucks. im listening to brand new, its not helping my emotions at all, its making me feel even more sad, too much slowness. thats about all i have to say for tonight. PLU.

Emily just broke up with me.

Bye.

SHOW THIS WEEKEND! TRAPPE YMCA, 6-11pm....6 BANDS FOR 6 DOLLARS!!

i'm bleeding all over the keyboard, the blood's dripping off my sliced up arm, the pain is endless and the throbing won't end.

who's better, choking victim or leftover crack?

wow last nights show was sooo good! we sucked but all the other bands were awesome, well i didnt get to see the last two but that doesnt matter. six foot smurf was amazing they were like ugh i dont know they were just incredible. they have gotten sooo much better and they're so tight now its unbelievable. plus they're all cuties. and then pat and shaw with their little ps/the cry babies thing, that was neat. they covered against me! and that was awesome and a half. ken was their with his pa so that was good. too bad ave went physco during kill you in the face's set and kept messing the pa up. i love ave lol. kill you in the face was really really really good too. they're cover of rock the 40oz was amazing and everyone, including pat, was moshing/hardcore dancing/ moving around. if they ever put out a full length im deffinatly buying it. i got to hang out with emily alot too so that made the show 10 times better.

i have to mow my neighbors lawn today, i really dont feel like it, i rather sit on my butt and eat an apple.

so no more shaw for tdt huh? well fine be that way shaw! lol just kidding. oh! i just got an email! be right back...

today was alright. i think i did really good on both of the test i had. i had health today and we learned about HIV. i walked pat to his bus because emily ran off to take some math thing. i have to go skateboard because i dont like sitting inside, but first i have to call ken. emily is my favorite. she is just too cool. math was stupid today we just sat and took notes, then alliy called me a dirtball, which was uncalled for since i was wearing a nice little sweater. miss brewster likes blink 182 over green day, what a freak. mr kelly made us do work in his class, what a surprise. i didnt finish the paper and its due tomorrow and i forgot to bring it home, drats. i have to leave now. 610 644 1414.

thats sam, i took that picture

i took this one too, they both have a special light effect on thats why they are the way they are

janelle took this one and the rest, thanks janelle

i took the last one

oatmeal with milk is always a good thing to have on a cold morning.

i finally got my pictures from mexico back. they're in b/w but i also have a ton in color, once i get my stupid digital fixed ill try to get those up.

thats a butterfly, it got messed up at the bottom

those are ruins

boats, this one got messed up at the bottom too

 

 

argh this one is messed up too, oh well, heres a taxi.
wow. mexico is an awesome place. i had a lot of fun there. i wish i was still there now. pennsylvania is too cold. pictures coming soon.

i leave for mexico tomorrow? spring break is going by fast! bp yesterday, pat me and shaw only, joe had school. we got a song down and started working on something else. it was fun. were finally getting recorded in may, and im setting up a show as soon as i get home from mexico. wow i hate being up this early in the morning, even tho its kinda cool since im the only one up and im not missing any of the day like i usually do when i wake up at 12. Emily's in pittsburg untill thursday night, which really sucks becuase now i wont see her untill next wednesday i think, back at school. well i have to go get to work. bye bye.

from ashes rise is a very good band that i like very much, you should like them too, if your into that kinda stuff ; ) today we had a half day at school, it was nice, we watched toy story 2 in spanish and i understood a couple words. i was on antisound reading the interview with six foot smurf, it was funny. my bus driver gave me some candy, snickers. i like milky ways better. does anyone like coconut? im really sleepy i think im going to take a nap. im going to the movies with Emily tonight, yippee!.......ana and kara are coming ::makes confused face:: 80d's had band practice today i wanted to go but couldnt silly parents. i had a bagel with cream cheese for lunch then i watched growing pains. heres a random picture i found, its cute, itd be cuter if it was shaw pat or joe tho they have funnier facial expressions. bye.

i got that off of antisound without asking, sorry kate.

hello! today was a fun day, i dont really know why, i was just in a really good mood all day. i had study hall with pete and ben and that was fun. i had band today and for the first time since i got my braces it didnt hurt to play my trumpet. pat faked sick to do a book report or something, i forgot to go to ecology club that wasnt too good. it was super nice out today. Emily just told me shes going to villa next year, i dont know why, i hate jesus school, i had to go to st. pats for like 7 years maybe. anyway half day friday, then spring break and mexico, bp monday tuesday and wednesday, thats right pat, you heard me. show last friday was fun, i didnt play my best but oh well i had loads of fun! i was in philly last night till 11 and im really tired, it stinks. thats about all i have to say, good-bye.

thank you to anyone and everyone who attened to show last night with tdt, sfs, toy, cr, and kyitf. we loved the support and such. hmm id have to say i enjoyed sixfootsmurf the most, and then thoughts of yesterday, they were pretty good too. sorry, wait VERY sorry to anyone who got lost on their way out to Trappe, i got a ride with pat and we stopped at subway to get directions, apparently there is no such thing as the "Trappe YMCA" its the "Springvalley YMCA" (i think). kill you in the face was really good, i liked them, capitol risk played too long, no one really came to the show. in the beginning tom, the guy helping us out, asked pat how many people we expected and his answer was "200" and i was like uh what try 100....little did we know the total number of kids would only add up to about 50, sorry tom. uh i took off my shirt during the set due to the extreme tempurature, sorry to anyone offended by that, i probally wont do it again...... boy do i love the bouncing souls....uh yeah any offers for a show? we'd love to play it! bye.

ok uh today was really really boring and not fun. i had an extra long history class and an extra long spanish class, then on top of that i had gym. for band we had some weird old guy and a study hall that was incredibly boring. i left after like 10 minutes or so with mike and we went to A lunch, i went to see Emily. i think that was actually the only fun part of my dad, talk to Emily. it was awesome. after A lunch ended i went back to study hall and the sub didnt even notice i had been gone for 30 minutes. uh then i think thats all, i went to lunch and ate some food. came home on the  bus. now im tired and my sister has a friend over. im going to go skateboard. happy trails. oh heres a random picture of some cutie i met over the internet, just kidding its jim morrison without a shirt ; )

argh tonight is a bad night, a bad night indeed. im supposed to be at a band practice right now, but instead im at a st patricks day party at grandma's house. boy oh boy the bands going to be pissed. hopefully i remember all our new songs at the show friday. i can practice after school any day this week my dad said, so hopefully we can have another practice before the show at trappe, that'd be AWESOME. anyway uh i got limewire today, kazaa was making me mad. ive already downloaded 6 songs, 3 bouncing souls songs, 2 7 seconds, a brand new song, and a saves the day song. i love the bouncing souls and 7 seconds rocks, uh the other 2 songs arent too great.

show this friday at the trappe ymca, as pat would say "be there or...not be there" he says something like that i think. its 5 dollars and i think it starts at 6. it should be a pretty good show, sfs has a new song thats supposed to be really good, and my band tdt has 3 new songs so that should be neat. i dont know about the other bands, i like kill you in the face so hopefully they'll have something interesting to listen to. capitol risk is emo, they'll be selling their full length, and i dont remember the other bands sorry. bye for now, have a nice night.

im at pats, were supposed to be having bp but im the only one here, i dont know where pat went. i have to go camping with pop tonight i dont kno why tho its snowy out. emilys going to the mall, with evan, and others. i hate evan. hey joe, if your reading this, when are you fighting him? uh im listening to thursday and they are singing, oh wait im listening to the bouncing souls now. tdt has a new emo-ish song and it sounds alot like the bouncing souls. i like it. wow this weekends going to suck, camping, then i have to see the middle school play, then a possible bp but i doubt it, my moms bitchy about band practices. good thing i dont have any school stuff due. pat and i bought pick spray paint and were going to paint our pa pink, it should be pretty cool. thats about it, happy trails.

today was fun. school was let out at 11:00. no gym. i went to patricks after school and that was fun. we went to bens and hung out there with sam and travis till jake showed up and then we went to travis' to skate. i took pictures and pat acted cool. after that pat and i went to subway for lunch, since subway is way cool. then we went to beams and i got a pick, i didnt have alot of money. we went home to pats after that, well actually first we stopped at clemens and the hardware store, but thats not important. back at pats we did stuff. that was my day. the domino theory has a community, it tdt_sucks, go join.

yeah so school was boring today, nothing really happened and i have to write an essay for health class. i fell asleep on the bus home, there weren't any middle schoolers making noise like there usually is. i got home and watched jimmy nuetron with my little sister, that was kinda cool. now im on the internet, talking and listening to music. happy saint patricks day. i have boy scouts tonight ::makes pissed off type face:: oh well ill make it fun. show march 26th, be there. bye.

thats a sticker hey look its pat! what a cutie!

 i just found that (its me at the nov. 8th show)

AHHHHH!! 

CAN SOMEONE PLEASE TELL ME HOW TO PUT UP PICTURES?

last night i went to the movies and saw a movie. it was really funny, and it was alot of fun. the best was seeing emily, and joe cuz hes a cutie. i think the movie was called starsky and hutch. it was funny, go see it. BAND PRACTICE IN 1 HOUR 51 MINUTES! yeah i'm really bored ive been up since like 8 i dont know why really, my moms yelling i have to go, bye.
Almost 200 people got killed today over in Spain, theres around 1500 people injured. I'm glad Bush is doing such a great got at getting rid of terrorist.
I GOT BRACES! and i hate them more than anything else ever....they're pink, and they hurt.

hi. my side band "in retrospect" kicked out our 2nd guitarist patrick gillie today. according to mike "the band isnt really working" so i dont even know if were really a band anymore, oh well, the one rehearsal i attended was fun. if we do stay together we need a vocalist, so anyone who can sing, email me or mike. one other thing, my main band "the domino theory" is making t-shirts, black and white, if anyone of you kids reading this has an idea for a logo type thing to put on them please email/call/talk to pat or i as soon as you can, thanks. bye.

last nights show was awesome! well i actually only listened to one band but yeah it was still good...i guess? i had a whole lot of fun tho, emily was there and we hung out most of the show, katie came with her and we had to wait for mike to come for like an hour...it sucked lol. i took loads of pictures of capitol risk, digital and regular, ill have em developed by monday hopefully. i hope everyone bought capitol risk's full length, it was only $2. uh thats all, bye.
emily and katie are baking cookies! band practice tonight at joes! yippee!

my new little band that im in finally figured out a name, in retrospect. we have practice sunday at carolyns and were hoping to get alot done, it should be fun. go to this http://www.antisoundpage.com
go to the emo show at the ywca saturday night, its going to rock! capitol risk's full length is for sale! $2! yay!
im at home, bored and im talking to patrick, now im going out to skate, bye.
